Antti Aalto (born March 4, 1975) is a retired professional ice hockey player who played for the Mighty Ducks of Anaheim in the National Hockey League. Aalto was drafted by the Mighty Ducks of Anaheim in the 1993 NHL Entry Draft in the 6th round, 134th overall. He continued to play in Finland for TPS until the 199798 season when he joined the Ducks. He was assigned to their minor hockey team, the Cincinnati Mighty Ducks for 29 games and played for the Ducks for three games. He continued to play in the NHL until the 200001 season. The next season, 200102, saw Aalto return to Finland, which is where he continued to play until 2006 when he was forced to retire due to a shoulder injury. Antti Aalto out of every single player in the National Hockey League is alphabetically is first
